And now follows a page from our Almanac on the Sunday Morning show: September 30, 1882, 136 years and a few days ago ...the birth day of the future physicist Johannes Wilhelm "Hans" Geiger in Germany.
Geiger developed a method of detecting and measuring radioactivity, and from this invention a device known as the Geiger counter was later developed.
